In life (
Figure 3
): Lateral surface of body red gray, head pale yellow. Dorsal and adipose fin bases dark brown. Dorsal fin yellowish, pectoral and pelvic fins light red. Dorsal, pectoral, and pelvic fins and head with many white conical tubercles. Caudal peduncle base and margin of upper and lower caudal fin rays red gray, tip and middle of caudal fin rays bright white. Nasal and maxillary barbels bright white.
